`1.10.0` animates from solely `scripts`, and may not have `animation_controllers` at all.

`cow.v1.0.entity.json` - `1.10.0`
```json
{
  "animations": {
    "setup": "animation.cow.setup.v1.0",
    "walk": "animation.quadruped.walk",
    "look_at_target": "animation.common.look_at_target",
    "baby_transform": "animation.cow.baby_transform"
  },
  "scripts": {
    "animate": [
      "setup",
      { "walk": "query.modified_move_speed" },
      "look_at_target",
      { "baby_transform": "query.is_baby" }
    ]
  }
}
```
`1.8.0` has animation controllers listed in `animation_controllers` that control all animations.

`bat.entity.json` - `1.8.0`
```json
{
  "animations": {
    "resting": "animation.bat.resting",
    "flying": "animation.bat.flying"
  },
  "animation_controllers": [
    { "move": "controller.animation.bat.move" }
  ]
}```

A variable for detecting when the entity is hurt (set to 1) using "is_hurt_color" in the render controller, credits to ZarkmendZan. The color defaults to black, so must be set manually if this isn't desired. The variable is also constantly set as long as the hurt color is active.
```json
"is_hurt_color": {
    "a": "variable.hurt = 1; return <desired value for alpha channel>;"
}
```

