**Simple error checking**  (Sync Code)
```js
try {
    // your code here
} catch ( error ) {
    console.warn(  error, error.stack  )
}
```


Normaly errors from async functions can not be checked by the above method

**Async error checking**
```js
some_async_function()
  .catch( error => { 
    console.error( error, error.stack ) 
  });
```

`"minecraft:render_offsets"` has two main parameters for the main hand and the off hand, each of which has two fields for the first-person and third-person views. These are defined by a position, a rotation, and a scale.
```json
"minecraft:render_offsets": {
  "main_hand": {
    "first_person": {
      "position": [0, 0, 0],
      "rotation": [0, 0, 0],
      "scale": [0, 0, 0]
    },
    "third_person":{
      "position": [0, 0, 0],
      "rotation": [0, 0, 0],
      "scale": [0, 0, 0]
    }
  },
  "off_hand": {
    "first_person": {
      "position": [0, 0, 0],
      "rotation": [0, 0, 0],
      "scale": [0, 0, 0]
    },
    "third_person": {
      "position": [0, 0, 0],
      "rotation": [0, 0, 0],
      "scale": [0, 0, 0]
    }
  }
}
```

